panels.description:
This measures the bytes submitted for processing. 
It reflects the ETL throughput, which is governed by concurrency settings.

The rate is governed by how fast the pipeline process daily job tasks.

This is fundamentally rather lumpy at the 10 minute level, so we average over 24h.  Aside from the fine-grained lumpiness, this should be the most stable of the throughput metrics, because it reflects the quantity of data, rather than the number or size of files.
panels.title: Byte Rate (24h avg)
